DISK OPERATION
--------------

The program uses the standard AMOS file requester for disk operations,so if
you are used to it then you should have no problems in loading or saving to
a seperate saved games disk.

Clicking  the  right mouse button while the disk is not being accessed will
display a number a device names (i.e C:  ,Formula-One-Challenge:, L:  ect).
Clicking  on  one  of these names with the left mouse button will display a
directory of the files on that device.

SAVING
------

All  F1C saved games are saved with a ".FO" extension after the filename,so
that  you  can  easily  identify your saved games.If you forgot to add this
yourself then it will automatically be added for you.

Do  not  save on the original F1C disk,but any formatted disk that does not
contain  important  data.It  is  advisable  before you start playing F1C to
format a disk and then use this for your saved games.
(For  instructions  on  how  to  format a disk see your introduction to the
Amiga manual supplied with your computer).

After saving a F1C game,replace the original F1C disk in df0: otherwise you
may encounter problems at a later stage.

Here is a detailed guide on saving your postion in F1C:- (Yawn -Baggy)

1)Format  a  disk  for  your  saved  games  using (CLI/SHELL,workbench,or a
  formatting utility (see AmigaDos manual for more details).

2)Play F1C until you wish to save,click on LOAD/SAVE from the menu,click on
  SAVE and wait for a full list of the original F1C disk to be diplayed and
  the disk drive to stop.

3)Swap disks if necessary and insert your blank (newly formatted disk).Wait
  a couple of seconds while the disk is checked by the computer.

4)Click  the  RIGHT  mouse  button to display a list of devicces.One of the
  items in the list should be the name of your blank disk i.e Empty.

5)Click  the  LEFT  mouse  button on the name of your blank disk and wait a
  couple of seconds for a list of the files on the disk to be displayed.

6)Click  on  "Game1.FO"  at  the bottom of the requster with the left mouse
  button and enter a name for your saved game and press [RETURN].Then click
  the left mouse button on O.K and your game will be saved.

7)You will be returned to the main menu when the game has saved.

8)When  the  disk  drive  light  goes  out,swap  the disks if necessary and
  replace the original F1C disk.

LOADING
-------

You  should  load  all  saved games froma disk other than your original F1C
disk and remember that all F1C games have a ".FO" extension to the filename
so they are easily identifiable.

Loading   is   similar   to  saving,so  please  read  the  detailed  saving
instructions  above.Wehn  a list of your saved games disk files appears,you
can  click  on  the  entries  in  the  list  and  then  on  O.K to load the
corresponding  file.Use  the  drag  bar to the left of the filenames in the
list  to  scroll  through  the  list if there are more enteries than can be
displayed in the given space.

After  loading  a F1C game,replace the original F1C disk in df0:  otherwise
you may encounter problems at a later stage.

