PLAYING TIPS
------------

*Dont  overspend  on  your  engine.Spend  around  60%  of your money on the
 engine.Dont  bother too much with the tyre manufacturers in your first few
 seasons (choose  the  cheapest!) and choose a driver with the rest of your
 money,leaving around 10,000 for other things.

*Learn  who  the  high  skilled  drivers are.The drivers tables are roughly
 ordered,but  experience  will  allow you to pick better drivers at bargain
 prices.

*Try  to  get  a second driver as quickly as possible,but make sure that he
 will qualify,if you are not confident that he will qualify then wait a few
 more races and get a better driver.

*Dont  be  too  eager  when  doing  pitstops,keep your finger off the mouse
 button until you are in the centre of the tyre!  Keep calm!

*If  the  weather  does  not change,and you are constantly making a pitstop
 during the race then check the grip/wear bars.Make your pitstop before half
 distance.Due  to a  lightning  fuel tyres will be more heavily used in the
 first half of the race compared with the second.

*Select  the  easist  difficulty  level  to  start with so that you can get
going.If you start doing well then select a harder difficulty level for the
next  season (can also help eo even out the teams when you are playing with
human friends).

